text: I was tweeting that all (100%) of the commodities on my screen were lower.

as in every (100%) of commodities sold off Doug.

I don't know what the hell is going on or where, but if you have a commodity screen up as I do all the time, you would be witnessing a near 100% selloff in every listed commodity and major foreign currency. This is indicative of an across the board deleveraging and is being e

executed in many commodities in a GET ME THE F>>>OUT manner. Somewhere, a butterfly has flapped its wings and an asteroid is creating another financial Yucatan peninsula ... maybe this near $trillion reverse repos really were a warning. Enjoy the weekend! @ferrotv

Tom In all likelihood there will ultimately be a deal between $VIAC and $CMCSA - in that event, you are far better off with the common rather than the convert (owing to the conversion premium being so large). To me $VIAC is $3 down and $25 up. I like the reward v risk!

@realmoney Based on our research, $VIAC fundamentals are improving relative to consensus expectations. This, along with the optionality of a deal (possibly with $CMCSA) qualifies the stock as our largest individual stock long now. Aggressively buying common and common today.
